  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "So I might be asking a silly question, but how do I view the source of a cookie?",
  "response": "It's not a silly question at all! Viewing the source of a cookie can help you understand how it is being used by a website. Here\u2019s how you can do this in various web browsers:\n\n### Google Chrome\n1. Right-click on the webpage and select **Inspect** (or press `Ctrl + Shift + I` or `Cmd + Option + I` on Mac).\n2. Go to the **Application** tab.\n3. In the left-hand sidebar, expand the **Cookies** section to view cookies for the current website.\n4. Click on the specific cookie to see its details, including its name, value, domain, path, expiration date, and other attributes.\n\n### Mozilla Firefox\n1. Right-click on the webpage and select **Inspect Element** (or press `Ctrl + Shift + I` or `Cmd + Option + I` on Mac).\n2. Go to the **Storage** tab.\n3. In the left-hand sidebar, find and click on **Cookies** to see cookies for the current website.\n4. You can view details about each cookie in the main panel.\n\n### Microsoft Edge\n1. Right-click on the webpage and select **Inspect** (or press `Ctrl + Shift + I`).\n2. Navigate to the **Application** tab.\n3. On the left sidebar, expand the **Cookies** section and select the website's cookies to view their details.\n\n### Safari\n1. Enable the Develop menu by going to **Preferences** > **Advanced** and selecting **Show Develop menu in menu bar**.\n2. Click on **Develop** in the menu bar and select **Show Web Inspector** (or press `Cmd + Option + I`).\n3. Navigate to the **Storage** tab.\n4. Expand the **Cookies** section to view cookies for the current website.\n\n### Additional Methods\n- **Browser Extensions**: There are various browser extensions available to manage and view cookies more easily if you find the built-in tools cumbersome.\n- **Command Line Tools**: For advanced users, tools like `curl` can be used to fetch cookies if you're working with APIs or web scraping.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to view and analyze the cookies set by the website you are visiting. If you have any more questions about cookies or anything else, feel free to ask!",
